  "detailedRequirements": "<p>Welcome to the&nbsp;<strong>Blogging on Communities</strong>&nbsp;challenge, brought to you by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.salesforce.com/\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 138, 0); text-decoration: none; outline: none; background: transparent;\">Salesforce.com</a>!</p>\n\n<p>There isn&#39;t a formal blogging &quot;module&quot; in Communities today &ndash; this is where we need your help to get creative on constructing a&nbsp;blogging platform. Therefore, the challenge here is to build out a robust blogging &quot;module&quot; that&nbsp;would have the fundamentals of constructing a blog post, a responsive UI, and also incorporate&nbsp;a Chatter feed under each blog post to collect/express any comments. The blog posts would&nbsp;also need to be available to be displayed both internally (in an internal Salesforce org) and&nbsp;externally (in a Community).</p>\n\n<p><span>We have completed Part 1 of this series as&nbsp;</span><span><a href=\"http://community.topcoder.com/tc?module=ProjectDetail&amp;pj=30045871\" style=\"line-height: 20.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"color:#FFA500\">Data Model</span></a></span><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 160, 122)\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 160, 122)\">.</span><span>&nbsp;We have also hosted a mock app&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 165, 0)\">&quot;</span><a href=\"http://warm-hollows-9976.herokuapp.com/\" style=\"line-height: 20.7999992370605px;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 165, 0)\">Blogging in Communities</span></a><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 165, 0)\">&quot;</span><span>.</span></p>\n\n<p><strong>For this Challenge</strong></p>\n\n<p>This challenge is the part of the Blogging in Communities series, to build out the Blogging Components on Salesforce.com</p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Blog List view\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Display blog List as per the Mock ups</li>\n\t\t<li>Display Blog auther Image and Title</li>\n\t\t<li>If user is the author of the Blog, display &quot;Edit Blog&quot; at the bottom of Title</li>\n\t\t<li>Pagination for the items</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Blog filters\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Allow to Sort Blogs by columns</li>\n\t\t<li>Allow to search blog by Topics and Blog Title</li>\n\t\t<li>Display Blog Status and Blog counts having that status\n\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t<li>Filter blogs when user clicks on the statuses</li>\n\t\t</ol>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Topics\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>If user clicks on a Title, Filter all the Blogs which has the same topic</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Implement navigation between Blog view and List and create Pages</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Data model source code and Unmanaged package is available in the forums.</strong></p>\n\n<h3>Resources</h3>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://developer.salesforce.com/gettingstarted\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 138, 0); text-decoration: none; outline: none; background: transparent;\"><strong>Salesforce Developer Website</strong></a>&nbsp;- Getting started with Salesforce development.</li>\n\t<li><span><strong><a href=\"https://developer.salesforce.com/page/An_Introduction_to_Visualforce\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 138, 0); text-decoration: none; outline: none; background: transparent;\">Introduction to Visualforce</a></strong></span></li>\n\t<li>User Anguar.js for UI</li>\n</ol>\n",
