  "finalSubmissionGuidelines": "<h2 style=\"margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px\">Code Guidelines</h2>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><strong>Aesthetics</strong>&nbsp;- Code must be clean (no commented code fragments, unused variables, etc.), tidy (4-space indents, ideally 80-char margins), and well-commented. Use clear and purposeful names for variables, classes, etc.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Unit Tests</strong>&nbsp;- You should target 90% code coverage for classes you develop, and all tests should pass.\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Please include meaningful assertions.</li>\n\t\t<li>Please also include one or more Systems tests. These should cover end-to-end usage, mimicking an end user&rsquo;s steps. &nbsp;Include comments</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li><strong>Scalability</strong>&nbsp;- Your app should support working with multiple records.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Demo-Ready</strong>&nbsp;- Your app should be ready to demo based on storyboard steps.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2 style=\"margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px\">Submission Deliverables</h2>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><strong>Source Code</strong>&nbsp;- Zip of source files (including all metadata files).</li>\n\t<li><strong>Unmanaged Package</strong>&nbsp;- Link to unmanaged package of same files.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Video</strong>&nbsp;- Video demonstrating setup of app (install + config), demo of app functionality, and overview of code.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Documentation</strong>&nbsp;- Provide documentation of setup (install/config) and steps for using the app.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n",
